President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Maine due to a severe storm and flooding that occurred from October 29 to November 1, 2017. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The counties of Cumberland, Franklin, Hancock, Kennebec, Knox, Lincoln, Oxford, Penobscot, Piscataquis, Sagadahoc, Somerset, Waldo, and York are eligible for federal funding on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures statewide are also eligible for federal funding. James N. Russo has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further damage assessments may result in additional designations for assistance. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.